{"ts": "2026-06-07T22:52:07.681454+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here are every CIFAR-10 model implemented in the `models/` directory along with its reported accuracy, drawn from the README's accuracy table:\n\n| Model | Accuracy |\n|---|---|\n| VGG16 | 92.64% |\n| ResNet18 | 93.02% |\n| ResNet50 | 93.62% |\n| ResNet101 | 93.75% |\n| RegNetX_200MF | 94.24% |\n| RegNetY_400MF | 94.29% |\n| MobileNetV2 | 94.43% |\n| ResNeXt29(32x4d) | 94.73% |\n| ResNeXt29(2x64d) | 94.82% |\n| SimpleDLA | 94.89% |\n| DenseNet121 | 95.04% |\n| PreActResNet18 | 95.11% |\n| DPN92 | 95.16% |\n| DLA | 95.47% |\n\n**Notes for picking a fine-tuning architecture:**\n\n- The `models/` directory also contains implementations of **EfficientNet**, **GoogLeNet**, **LeNet**, **MobileNetV1**, **PNASNet**, **SENet**, **ShuffleNet**, and **ShuffleNetV2**, but these are **not listed** in the README's accuracy table, so their CIFAR-10 accuracies are not reported.\n- If you want the best-reported baseline to start from, **DLA (95.47%)** tops the list. For a good balance of accuracy and simplicity, **DenseNet121** and **PreActResNet18** are solid choices with >95% accuracy.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 484, "prompt_tokens": 5902, "total_tokens": 6386, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 62, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 3264, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0005139792, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0003784592, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00013552}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780872722-aASl80e9YKRnvVHNzekK", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": nu